The end of the heart and eyes are only this amazing landscape, unknowingly has been climbing up. If you have time, take a walk to Taroko National Park. Use your eyes to see the scenery you wouldn't normally see, listen to the sounds of nature, and enjoy the comfort of the whole person bathed in the mountains and waters.

*** With its ineffable grandeur, Taroko is without a doubt the gem of Hualien.

It has to be said that the scope of Kenting Park is very large. You can spend about half a day here walking and exploring.
There are many natural ecology here, as well as rare creatures, plants, insects, natural forms, etc., which are hardly seen in other places. If you have a lot of time, you can take a look. I think this might be one of the national parks I've been to. It's a place I really like. The nature here is really beautiful and will make people feel eye-opening. There is a feeling of discovering a new world, which is amazing.
But I have to say that the moving line planning inside feels that it can be maintained better. There are many routes in it, all very similar, but I couldn't find the exit and almost got lost inside. 😂
In addition, there is no signal at all when the navigation is turned on.

knowledge_graph.description: Jiufen is a mountain town in northeastern Taiwan, east of Taipei. most_relevant.description: The ferry journey was fun and nice way to see the lake. Due to drought, the water level is low but the weather was good. Very scenic and leisure walk around the lake.
Great place with lots of places to take photos. Unusual weather, cold wind but hot sun. Famous tea eggs on one of the sides as well.
Beautiful, scenic place. Best to avail the sun moon lake pass which you may use as tickets in getting around the area. There are also many places to see, and not crowded.
Really peaceful scenery, especially in the early morning. Comfortable weather and fascinating landscape. There are many boat tours you can take to explore the lake. Highly recommended!

It’s a very touristy place. Not much to do either. Hiking trail are closed due to maintenance. Only available was like 2 km long… alternatively you can walk by the highway but it’s not a pleasant experience ( no need to mention neither tranquil xD). There are few shows with souvenirs, early closing and late opening restaurants.. the lake itself shaped like sun and moon ( there are two parts) remains beautiful but for someone who doesn’t like hiring guides, purchasing vouchers for cable cars and cruises, I just did not found what I was looking for ( nature, indigenous people outside of huge amusement park for kids). Coming here was not worth my time, money and effort. I do not recommend visiting… there were even no street foods, can you imagine that?

Fun place! We rented bikes and rode around half the lake before taking the ferry back to where we started. Some places along the route can get quite steep, but it balances out with the scenery and downhill slopes in between. Worth the trip!

Rent a bike, bike around the lake, stop at the visitor’s center. This is the best sunny day activity! Difficulty: 3 out of 10
